p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    28\cdot\left( -{\frac{2}{7}} \right)
    \amp =\frac{28}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{2}{7}}\right) \amp \hbox{We can divide both the first numerator and the second denominator by 7.}\\
    \amp =\frac{4}{1} \cdot \left(-{\frac{2}{1}}\right)\\
    \amp ={-8}
    \end{aligned}}
